SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 885
By Bailey
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Jake Stinnett on
winning the 2026 TSSAA Division I, Class A
State wrestling championship in the 120-pound
weight class.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
salute those student athletes who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished
themselves as true champions of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, Jake Stinnett, a student at Upperman High School, recently won the 2026
TSSAA Division I, Class A State wrestling championship in the 120-pound weight class, held at
the Williamson County Ag Exposition Arena in Franklin; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Stinnett epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he has
achieved a high level of success in athletic competition while demonstrating great character
both on and off the wrestling mat; and
WHEREAS, his perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent not only made
possible a championship season but also surely bode well for his future success; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Jake Stinnett as an
exceptional state champion of whom we can all be proud; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Jake Stinnett on winning
the 2026 TSSAA Division I, Class A State wrestling championship in the 120-pound weight
class and extend to him our best wishes for every future success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
